Glossary<br /> <br /> 
Market capitalization: total value of the issued shares of a publicly traded company. Equal to the current share price times the number of shares outstanding. This represents the public consensus on the value of a company’s equity.<br /> 
Large-cap (capitalization): large companies (market capitalization > $10 billion)<br /> 
Mid-cap: medium-sized companies (market capitalization between $2 and $10 billion)<br /> 
Small-cap: small companies (market capitalization between $250 million and $2 billion)<br /> 
